msgid "Gobots"
msgstr ""

#. [side]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:843
msgid "Allies"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:898
msgid ""
"Well, it's the last part of the swamp we have not searched. If we do not find"
" the goblin's lair here, we will have to go back..."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:902
msgid ""
"If anyone notices anything out of place in this swamp, tell us. That might be"
" the hint we are looking for."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:917
msgid "Potions"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:942
msgid "Aaaahhhh!!!"
msgstr ""

#. [0]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:970
msgid ""
"We fell into a hole and into some kind of old temple. There seem to be Vine "
"Tigers."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:985
msgid "There's someone in the hut."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:991
msgid ""
"Ah finally! I was starting to think all humans were gone. It looks like the "
"country was invaded by monsters!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1032
msgid "I'm Nrifyo, a young mage."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1049
msgid ""
"I arrived here following the trail of the gold pinched during Eukhac’s bowman"
" tournament."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1076
msgid ""
"Listen, I know I am young for a mage, but I know one or two spells and I’m "
"ready to help you for a decent price. Let's say, 49000 gold."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1082
msgid "Honestly, I know my job! I only need someone to watch my back."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1084
msgid "We would be glad to have you with us."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1096
msgid "I am afraid you don't have enough gold to hire me."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Nrifyo
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1147
msgid ""
"By the stars, could have my luck changed? Nrifyo, mage apprentice, at your "
"service!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1167
msgid "Well… Yes, it was to be expected!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1173
msgid ""
"I can’t see straight anymore, with all the hits my poor nut received, lately."
" See you around."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1206
msgid "There's a witch in the hut."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=trader
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1217
msgid "Come in, come in! I won't hurt you."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=trader
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1221
msgid "Oooh! Look at these beautiful men. Ain’t they magnificent in their suits? "
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=trader
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1225
msgid "Admire their proud air. Their look neither bat nor falter. "
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=trader
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1229
msgid ""
"But Meixmi knows how to catch their attention. She has a profusion of "
"curative balms. "
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=trader
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter4/32_Eastern_Swamp.cfg:1270
msgid ""
"My potions are coming out of the caldron. Against a few coins, they will heal"
