msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=trader
#. [object]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:1823
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/utils/item_list.cfg:12978
msgid "Great Healing Potion"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2028
msgid ""
"It looks like it has been corrupted, like the ones we encountered in the "
"swamp. But this time, the corruption feels... natural."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2032
msgid ""
"There must be some kind of mad wose in this forest corrupting neighboring "
"trees."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2044
msgid "It looks like that tree was completely rotten."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2048
msgid ""
"It must have been the mad wose that corrupted all the other trees. The forest"
" should be more peaceful now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2052
msgid "Well, I mean, apart from the rest of the wildlife trying to kill us."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2065
msgid "There was a cyclops in the house."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2084
msgid "There are stairs going down into a tunnel."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2094
msgid "It must be the flooded tunnels Oboavlidlu told us about."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2098
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2137
msgid "Should we go down there?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2100
msgid ""
"Yes, we should try to find the treasure hunters. Who knows what happened to "
"them?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2128
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2167
msgid "No, we have no time for that. We need to go down the old temple road."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2139
msgid "Yes, let's see where it leads."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2185
msgid "Let's continue. We need to reach Oof fortress as quickly as possible."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2199
msgid "How many walking trees are there in this forest?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2208
msgid "There are a lot of trees, but not all of them are wose."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2212
msgid ""
"On the plus side, as you have seen, the wose are quite slow, so we just need "
"to progress faster than they are coming for us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2216
msgid ""
"Even better, if we could get rid of the wose that is spreading the corruption"
" to the forest, the trees should then leave us in peace."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario], id=35b_Flooded_Tunnels
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:4
msgid "Flooded Tunnels"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:51
msgid "Explore the tunnels"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:65
msgid "Find the treasure hunters"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:79
msgid "Report back to Oboavlidlu"
msgstr ""

#. [side], type=Saurian Matriarch LoI
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:143
msgid "Matriarch"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:958
msgid "Looks like those tunnels have been abandonned for a while."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:962
msgid ""
"On the other hand, I don't see much dust, so it seems we are not the first "
"ones going there, humans or creatures."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:966
msgid "Lets look for a way out and hope it takes us closer to our goal."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:972
msgid ""
"So those are the famous flooded tunnels. They don't look so flooded from "
"here, although the air is quite moist."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:976
msgid "Our goal is to find the treasure hunters and then report back to Oboavlidlu."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:980
msgid "Let's make it quick, our main mission is of dire importance."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1003
msgid "This wall looks more recent. Should I tried to demolish it?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1017
msgid "Looks like there's a room on the other side. "
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1022
msgid "We don't have the tools for that."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1046
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1089
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1132
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1175
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1290
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1346
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1402
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1527
msgid "There is a huge metal door. Should I open it?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1065
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1108
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1151
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1194
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1266
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1322
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1378
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1421
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1546
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1657
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1675
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1726
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1744
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1896
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1932
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1968
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2004
msgid "No, not right now."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1223
msgid "There are two huge metal doors. Should I open them?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1261
msgid "There're opened."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1437
msgid "There're corpses in there."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1447
msgid ""
"I'm afraid they are those of the treasure hunter we were supposed to look "
"for. They were probably killed by the saurians."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1451
msgid ""
"Let's go back to the surface and warn Oboavlidlu so that he can give them a "
"decent burial."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1458
msgid "Poor fellows. It looks like they were killed by the saurians."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1464
msgid ""
"It looks like one of their horses survived though. Maybe we could take him "
"with us?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1503
msgid "No, leave it be. It might be someone's horse."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1570
msgid "It looks like this wall is made of earth. Should I try to dig through?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1584
msgid "There seems to be a corridor behind."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1589
msgid "No, we don't have the tools for that."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1644
msgid "A second lever appear on the floor."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1650
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1670
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1739
msgid "It's blocked."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1721
msgid "Part of the opposite wall slid down."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1765
msgid "What's that?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Amin
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1780
msgid "Goblin contraption, that's what it's. Let me grab my hammer."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1784
msgid "Wait! What's the purpose of it?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Amin
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1788
msgid "Who cares? I say we remove it for the undersurface of the earth."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1792
msgid "Amin..."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Amin
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1796
msgid ""
"Ok, ok. It looks like a giant steam engine. And it looks like it is running. "
"I have no idea what it powers though."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1800
msgid "What's a steam engine?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Amin
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1804
msgid ""
"A device that produces mechanical energy with water and fire. But I would in "
"no way trust one of goblin fabrication, it could explode anytime, killing "
"everyone in the tunnels."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1808
msgid "But you understand how it works, don't you?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Amin
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1812
msgid ""
"I know how a normal one works, not the weird goblin death machines. But I can"
" have a look if you want. It will not be said that a dwarf will fail to "
"understand how an engine works, be it a goblin one."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1816
msgid "Please do."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Amin
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1838
msgid ""
"I have never seen such a terrible job at making an engine. I have no idea how"
" it has not exploded yet. I assume the numerous leaks prevent the pressure "
"from rising high enough to do so.\n"
"                                        Anyway, if you really want to make it"
" do whatever it is supposed to, you should turn the four big wheel that are "
"placed on each side of the engine. Then Of bless us for what will happen."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1849
msgid ""
"It looks a bit like the goblin engines. I wonder what it does and how it "
"ended up here."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1853
msgid "It looks like there some kind of big wheel on each side."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1857
msgid "Maybe something will happen if we turn each of them."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1883
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1919
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1955
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:1991
msgid "There is a huge wheel. Should I turn it?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2021
msgid "Should we go?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2053
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2332
msgid "Yes, we are wasting our time here."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2057
msgid "Let's go back and take the main road instead."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2097
msgid "No, I am sure there is another exit."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2132
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2556
msgid "Yes, this exit should bring us closer to our goal."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2249
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2689
msgid "Well, it looks like I was wrong, this was not a shortcut."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2253
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2693
msgid ""
"I have been misled by all the tunnels and caves we have used as shortcut or "
"detour since the beginning of our journey."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2257
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2697
msgid "Let's continue on the main road instead."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2336
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2953
msgid "There is no sign of the treasure hunters and our mission is urgent."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2340
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2959
msgid "Let's go back and continue down the old temple road."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Oboavlidlu
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2469
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2701
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2893
msgid "Back already? Have you found the treasure hunters?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2473
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2705
msgid ""
"I'm sorry but we've seen no sign of that and we have to time to look longer "
"after then."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Oboavlidlu
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2477
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2709
msgid ""
"I understand. Still, I hope we will find out what happened to them. In these "
"difficult times, it would be regrettable to lose their... support."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2481
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2713
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2916
msgid "Goodbye. Now, let's continue our journey down the old temple road."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2521
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2753
msgid "No, we have not found the treasure hunters yet."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2560
msgid ""
"There is no sign of the treasure hunters and our mission is too urgent to "
"waste more time here."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2764
msgid "Yes, we should go report to Oboavlidlu."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2897
msgid "I'm sorry but they are dead."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Oboavlidlu
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2901
msgid "You found them dead? That’s marvelous!... Hmm... It is a bit unfortunate."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Oboavlidlu
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2905
msgid ""
"I knew they were not the kind to leave without saying goodbye. Please take "
"this modest sum in return for your help."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Oboavlidlu
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2912
msgid ""
"Oddaty and I will have to go there without delay to make sure to provide a..."
" hmm... decent burial to those poor lads."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/35b_Flooded_Tunnels.cfg:2943
msgid "We are wasting our time here."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario], id=36_Old_Temple_Road
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:4
msgid "Old Temple Road"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:33
msgid "Find the entrance of the old temple"
msgstr ""

#. [side], type=Deathlord LotI
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:595
msgid "Undead Leader"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:641
msgid "The road seems to continue north. I assume the temple is in the forest."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:645
msgid "From what I recall, it is actually in a clearing."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:649
msgid "Then I will be glad when we get out of this forest. It is oppressing."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:668
msgid "Undead. What a surprise."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:672
msgid "It is not like we were supposed to go fight a powerful necromancer."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:676
msgid "At least, we know it is the right way..."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:680
msgid ""
"Let's try not to keep any undead behind us. I'm already afraid that they will"
" warn Isut about us, I would rather not have them attack us in the back at "
"the worst time."
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:685
msgid "Find the entrance of the Old Temple"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:690
msgid "Kill all undead"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:717
msgid ""
"South-east: The Scavenger’s Trading Post\n"
"North: Oof Fortress"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:741
msgid "Look! It looks like the entrance of the Old Temple is here."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:761
msgid "We don't have more time to waste here. Let's go!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:765
msgid "We need to reach Oof's fortress before captain Soimaql get overwhelmed."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:769
msgid ""
"I'm a bit afraid of the tentacle guardians we were warned about, let's hope "
"we can cross without meeting them."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:781
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:909
msgid "Wait for us! We are still fighting the undead here!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:803
msgid "I don't see any more undead around here. I think we can continue safely."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:807
msgid ""
"Well, I mean, as safely as we can with a necromancer and tentacle monsters on"
" our way."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:811
msgid "Let's get into the Old Temple."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:827
msgid "I think we are lost. We should have stayed on the main road."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:831
msgid "Now, we will arrive too late to save captain Soimaql, and the kingdom."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario], id=37_Old_Temple
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:4
msgid "Old Temple"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:27
msgid "Cross the old temple"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:32
msgid "Defeat both enemy leaders"
msgstr ""

#. [objectives]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:45
msgid "Petrification can be healed in this scenario."
msgstr ""

#. [side], type=Fury LoI
#. [unit_type], id=Fury LoI, race=demon-loti, gender=female
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:101
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Fury.cfg:4
msgid "Fury"
msgstr ""

#. [side], type=Mine Worm LoI
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:117
msgid "Worms"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:428
msgid ""
"So, this is the Old Temple. It looks like it was once majestic. But now it's "
"just... old"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:432
msgid ""
"Anyway, we need to cross it to reach Oof's fortress and save Captain Soimaql."
" We must expect to have to fight a ``tentacle monster'', although I have no "
"idea what it might encompass."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:436
msgid "And undead. Undead too. Why not undead, indeed?..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:440
msgid ""
"I can feel a strong force of black magic north. There must be a powerful "
"necromancer there."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:444
msgid ""
"If we believe in the reports, Isut must be at the fortress already, meaning "
"it is either one of his lackeys or one of his allies."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:448
msgid ""
"I guess we will find out if we meet them. Although that would probably be a "
"good idea to defeat them: I would rather not have undead behind AND in front "
"of us."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:473
msgid ""
"What's this monstrosity? It is a bit like a Mine Worm, but much bigger and "
"scarier."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:477
msgid "I am afraid it might be a beast called a Mehsi."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:481
msgid "Some scholars theorize it to be the adult form of the Mine Worm."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Amin
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:485
msgid ""
"I refuse to believe that! Implying us dwarves have been struggling with mere "
"younglings for generation!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Amin
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:489
msgid "Bloody scholars! Disrespecting the entire dwarvish race."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:493
msgid ""
"Mine Worm or not, be careful everyone, because it looks like it could eat any"
" of us whole. Even a horse..."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:518
msgid ""
"So, this must be the famous tentacle monster. Be careful everyone one, it "
"made the legionary nearly mad."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:534
msgid "Wait, there are two of them?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:538
msgid ""
"Or could it be that those are not the tentacle monster and that something "
"even scarier is?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:562
msgid ""
"Oh! So, this is the tentacle monster! No wonder that poor legionary went mad "
"fleeing that thing."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:566
msgid ""
"Unlucky us, it looks like it's blocking the exit. I'm not sure we will be "
"able to pass without fighting it..."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=necromancer
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:586
msgid ""
"You may have found me, but you will never be able to defeat Mal Wlicikoyl, "
"Commander Isut's second in command."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:590
msgid "Well, at least we know who we are facing."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:594
msgid ""
"It would be a great victory to defeat him as it would probably impair their "
"undead army."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=necromancer
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:607
msgid "You may have defeated me, but never will you defeat Commander Isut!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:628
msgid "It looks like all the undead he was commanding are crumbling to dust."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:641
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:657
msgid "It looks like some undead are still standing."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:645
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:661
msgid ""
"Those are probably directly controlled by Isut. There should not be many that"
" far from the fortress."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:678
msgid "That's it! We defeated the tentacle monster!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:687
msgid ""
"We might not have defeated the necromancer, but once we will have defeated "
"Isut, it should be easy for the Legion to clean the Temple."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:691
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:707
msgid "Now, let's get out of here, find this Isut and save Captain Soimaql!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/37_Old_Temple.cfg:703
msgid ""
"Now that we have defeated both the monster and the necromancer, people should"
" be able to use this way again once Isut is defeated."
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:44
msgid "Defeat Isut"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:53
msgid "Enter Oof's fortress"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:65
msgid "Defeat all undead"
msgstr ""

#. [side], type=Draug
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:144
msgid "Undead Hordes"
msgstr ""

#. [side], type=Dwarvish Steelclad
#. [side], type=Duelist
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:382
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter6/39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:49
msgid "Defenders"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:443
msgid "I'm glad to finally be out of this cave. It was oppressing."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:447
msgid "Probably because of how old everything was in there."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:451
msgid "And undead. Undead too. And tentacle monsters."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:455
msgid ""
"Anyway, we must not be far from the fortress now. We need to find Isut "
"quickly and defeat him before the fortress fall."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:470
msgid "East: Oof Fortress"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:488
msgid ""
"East: Oof Fortress, Scavenger’s Trading Post\n"
"West: Eastern Swamp"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:507
msgid ""
"North: Oof Fortress\n"
"South: Scavenger’s Trading Post"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:529
msgid "That wolf looks weird."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:533
msgid ""
"It looks as if it was possessed. Or rather as if something was wearing a wolf"
" like a costume."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:547
msgid "I found Isut!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Isut
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:557
msgid ""
"Finally, adversaries to match up to myself. I thought I would die from "
"boredom fighting those pathetic legionaries."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Isut
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:561
msgid "We will see if you make better adversaries than the other humans."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:585
msgid "Well, looks like we are trapped. Not like we intended to flee anyway."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:589
msgid "Fight!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:614
msgid "We did it! Isut is no more!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:627
msgid "Aren't his undead supposed to fall into dust or something?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:631
msgid "They should be. But I am not versed in orcish necromancy so I could be wrong."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:635
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:675
msgid ""
"They seems to wander aimlessly now at least, which means the fortress should "
"be safe."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:639
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:653
msgid "So, we did it?! We saved the fortress?! Hurray!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Teumiuxe, Csia
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:643
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:657
msgid "We should go there to meet Captain Soimaql now."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:647
msgid "Shouldn't we kill the remaining undead before?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:667
msgid "Aren't Isut undead supposed to haven fallen into dust or something?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:671
msgid ""
"They should have. But I am not versed in orcish necromancy so I could be "
"wrong."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:679
msgid "We should probably kill the remain undead anyway."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:696
msgid "I found something in the house."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:734
msgid "I'm Ubidaiubua, a roving mage and a Traveler."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:749
msgid ""
"Thoze foolz couldn’t even recognize their mother…I’ve an exzellent magic "
"againzt the Ockz but thoze bloody legionariez don’t truzt me under the "
"pretext that I’m a Traveler, a ztranger!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:753
msgid "My couzin Bta is captive inside. I must make sure she’z alright."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:772
msgid "Maybe they will let me in if I’m with you… "
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:776
msgid "I’m willing to zell my zpells to YOU, for 78000."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:780
msgid "Deal?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:792
msgid "I am afraid you don't have enough gold for a mage like me."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:815
msgid "I am zorry, but you zeem to be quite a party already."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:836
msgid "Ubidaiubua will remember you, pal! Thiz iz a promize!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:840
msgid "Let’z go in the fortrezz together and zee what thre’z to zee!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:844
msgid "You can now recruit red mages."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:857
msgid "Then, leave. You don’t trust Ubidaiubua."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:861
msgid "You’re not worthy of the zervicez of the wonderful roving mage I am."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:897
msgid "Here is the fortress. Let's meet Captain Soimaql."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:934
msgid "I think it was the last undead around."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:938
msgid "Let's go to the fortress then."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter5/38_Isut.cfg:1034
msgid "No! We arrive too late, the fortress has already fallen!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario], id=39_Oofs_Fortress
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter6/39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:4
msgid "Oof's Fortress"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter6/39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:15
msgid ""
"The greatest threat for Oof’s fortress disappeared with Isut death, but the "
"serious danger of the reappearance of this ancient malevolent spirit "
"seriously torments our hero."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter6/39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:156
msgid "Excuse me, are you Captain Soimaql?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Soimaql
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter6/39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:160
msgid ""
"I am. Thank you for saving what is left of the Legion that was defending the "
"fortress."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Soimaql
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter6/39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:164
msgid ""
"One hundred and eighty-two dead… And all this because a dummy disobeyed "
"orders!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Soimaql
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter6/39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:172
msgid ""
"A scout had noticed the Ocks in the wood several weeks ago, but he kept quiet"
" from fear that the others may accuse him of seeing ghosts."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter6/39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:176
msgid "The Ocks?! Ain't they supposed to be all dead and buried for centuries?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Soimaql
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/scenarios/chapter6/39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:180
msgid ""
"Everybody believed those creatures had well and truly disappeared for three "
"centuries."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ancient Dark Wose LoI, race=wose
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ancient_Dark_Wose.cfg:4
msgid "Ancient Dark Wose"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ancient Dark Wose LoI, race=wose
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ancient_Dark_Wose.cfg:16
msgid ""
"It has always been all too known to all creatures that nature is not only a "
"nurturing mother; it can also be cruel, violent and destructive. It's unknown"
" what makes a wose become corrupted, but one thing is certain: nowhere else "
"does nature's rage becomes more evident than in an Ancient Dark Wose."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ancient_Dark_Wose.cfg:31
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/HerbDiseased.cfg:29
msgid "crush"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Direrat LoI, race=monster
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Direrat.cfg:4
msgid "Direrat"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Direrat LoI, race=monster
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Direrat.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Much larger than the giant rats which often inhabit caves, these vermin can "
"injure an armed civilian, and can prove frustratingly aggressive on any "
"footing. On top of being notably very aggressive at night, these creatures "
"pose much of a threat to any serious fighter."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Direrat.cfg:24
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Fury.cfg:46
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Hellboar.cfg:50
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Wyvern.cfg:101
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/d3_Medusa_Witch.cfg:43
msgid "bite"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Dragonguard LoI, race=steelhive
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Dragonguard.cfg:4
msgid "Gobot Dragonguard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Dragonguard LoI, race=steelhive
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Dragonguard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"It is not clear why the Dragonguards are called what they are, a name stolen "
"from the dwarves. Some speculate that the name comes from their weapon of "
"choice, these strange staves that belch fire and death. Others have surmised "
"that it is because such weapons would be a threat against even a true Dragon,"
" should such a thing be seen again in the known world. Whatever the case, it "
"is for these weapons that the guardians of the great Goblin citadels are both"
" renowned and feared; weapons that have broken the mightiest of warriors with"
" a storm of blows."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Dragonguard.cfg:27
msgid "thunderstick"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Elder Dark Wose LoI, race=wose
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Elder_Dark_Wose.cfg:4
msgid "Elder Dark Wose"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Elder Dark Wose LoI, race=wose
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Elder_Dark_Wose.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Filled with hatred and malice, these beings will destroy anything that is "
"foolish enough to stand in their way."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Foul Dark Wose LoI, race=wose
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Foul_Dark_Wose.cfg:4
msgid "Foul Dark Wose"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Foul Dark Wose LoI, race=wose
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Foul_Dark_Wose.cfg:16
msgid ""
"When a Dark Wose lives long enough, its corruption makes it rot from the "
"inside. This is making it even more powerful and aggressive."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Frozen Lich LoI, race=undead
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Frozen_Lich.cfg:4
msgid "Frozen Lich"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Frozen Lich LoI, race=undead
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Frozen_Lich.cfg:29
msgid ""
"A lich is the physical embodiment of black magic’s first goal: the quest to "
"achieve immortality. Though a great deal is sacrificed in the rebirth, in "
"becoming a lich one cheats death of that which truly gives it terror. For it "
"is the mind that is retained, and the spirit which follows, though the body "
"may wither away.\n"
"\n"
"It is not known, save perhaps by the inner circles of necromancy, whether "
"life is prolonged indefinitely or simply extended. The fact that this "
"question can be raised at all is a testament to the magnitude of what their "
"order has achieved.\n"
"\n"
"This lich transformed in the Ice Cave, conferring it specails powers based on"
" cold."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=melee
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Frozen_Lich.cfg:45
msgid "cold touch"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Frozen_Lich.cfg:57
msgid "chill tempest"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Fury LoI, race=demon-loti, gender=female
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Fury.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Furies were once very beautiful beings, legend said that a man who looked at "
"them was not able to keep a clear mind because of their beauty. But when they"
" turned against the gods they were cursed and turned into monstrosities. "
"Their gaze is so terrible that any being looking at them will be paralyzed in"
" fear. They are sourrounded by a dark aura that weakens and kills enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Fury.cfg:59
msgid "sword"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Fury.cfg:73
msgid "gaze"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Fury.cfg:87
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Fury.cfg:101
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/d3_Medusa_Witch.cfg:57
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/d3_Medusa_Witch.cfg:71
msgid "petrify"
msgstr ""

#. [petrifies]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Fury.cfg:110
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/d3_Medusa_Witch.cfg:80
msgid "petrifies"
msgstr ""

#. [petrifies]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Fury.cfg:111
msgid ""
"Petrify:\n"
"                        This attack petrifies the target, turning it to "
"stone. Units that have been petrified may not move or attack. It will wear "
"off after a turn."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Green Crystal LoI, race=abstraction
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Green_Crystal.cfg:5
msgid "Green Crystal"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Green Crystal LoI, race=abstraction
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Green_Crystal.cfg:31
msgid ""
"A Green Crystal is a Shard that has emerged from a high concentration of mana"
" located in a cave.\n"
"\n"
"Crystals are bound to their mana geyser, so they cannot go out of the cave "
"they were born in. Crystals are crystalline in nature and so have unusual "
"resistances. A consequence of this is their immunity to Drain, Poison and "
"Plague."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Grenadeer LoI, race=steelhive
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Grenadeer.cfg:4
msgid "Gobot Grenadeer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Grenadeer LoI, race=steelhive
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Grenadeer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This curious machine looks like a Dwarven Thunderguards made out of metal. "
"The Dwarven Thunderguards are famed for their curious weaponry, these strange"
" staves of wood and iron that make a thunderous noise in their anger. The "
"machinations behind this weaponry are a mystery, a secret taken to the grave "
"by the dwarves of Knalga who wield them, and are assumed to have even forged "
"them. The most that is known are reports of dwarves pouring a strange black "
"dust into the mouth of their weapons, which some say is a food to fuel the "
"beast imprisoned within. It seems that goblins tried to replicate them, "
"leading to a strange machine able to shoot explosive spheres.\n"
"\n"
"Though a single shot from these ‘boomsticks’ can take several minutes to "
"prepare, the results are seen by the goblins as being well worth the wait."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Grenadeer.cfg:29
msgid "boomstick"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Hell Boar LoI, race=monster
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Hellboar.cfg:4
msgid "Hell Boar"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Hell Boar LoI, race=monster
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Hellboar.cfg:35
msgid ""
"It is said that those boars were bread by the Ocks to be used as yoke for "
"their wagons. Since those were vanquished, they found a place of residence in"
" the Black Forest, where they compete with bears for food."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Hellboar.cfg:59
msgid "tusk"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Diseased Herb Spirit LoI, race=wose
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/HerbDiseased.cfg:5
msgid "Diseased Herb Spirit"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Diseased Herb Spirit LoI, race=wose
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/HerbDiseased.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Most of the herb spirits use their power to repel insect infestations but a "
"few of them welcome the insects in so that they can use them as game pieces "
"or suddenly expel them as a method of attack."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/HerbDiseased.cfg:38
msgid "swarm"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Bat LoI, race=elemental
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Bat.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Bat"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Bat LoI, race=elemental
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Bat.cfg:20
msgid ""
"The most vicious, predatory, and successful of the creatures born in the ice "
"cave."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Bat.cfg:37
msgid "ice fangs"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Bowman LoI, race=elemental, gender=male
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Bowman.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Bowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Bowman LoI, race=elemental, gender=male
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Bowman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Born in the cold of the ice cave, ice bowmen are fearsome enemies. The great "
"strength allows them to attack with high range and power."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Bowman.cfg:37
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Master_Bowman.cfg:37
msgid "ice longbow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Golem LoI, race=elemental
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Golem.cfg:5
msgid "Ice Golem"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Golem LoI, race=elemental
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Golem.cfg:31
msgid ""
"Ice elementals, once gathering enough elemental essence, can absorb more ice "
"and grow larger and stronger. Although they are weak, they can take massive "
"amounts of damage before they are destroyed to shards."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Guard LoI, race=elemental
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Guard.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Guard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Guard LoI, race=elemental
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Guard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Ice Guards are picked from the best swordsmen in the ice cave. They function "
"as bodyguards and commanders. Their reliability and mastery of close combat "
"are their best assets, for which they are well-renowned."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Guard.cfg:39
msgid "ice longsword"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Hero LoI, race=troll
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Hero.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Troll Hero"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Hero LoI, race=troll
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Hero.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Some ice trolls are born with an exceptional share of the strength and "
"vitality that characterizes their race. In a society where might makes right,"
" those of their ilk revere them as heroes."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Hero.cfg:35
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Warrior.cfg:35
msgid "hammer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Master Bowman LoI, race=human, gender=male
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Master_Bowman.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Master Bowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Master Bowman LoI, race=human, gender=male
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Master_Bowman.cfg:32
msgid ""
"Born in the cold of the ice cave, ice master bowmen have reached the zenith "
"of their art, inasmuch as any ice bowman is capable. Armed with a great ice "
"bow, these warriors crown battalions of ice bowmen with their presence, "
"bringing down many a foe with their well-aimed shots. Of the many races in "
"the world, only the elves surpass them in archery, and their human "
"counterparts have speculated, perhaps in envy, that this is only by dint of "
"age."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Swordsman LoI, race=elemental
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Swordsman.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Swordsman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Swordsman LoI, race=elemental
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Swordsman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Born into the cold of the icecave, this unit is an experienced warrior "
"equipped with a sturdy broadsword made of ice."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Swordsman.cfg:38
msgid "ice sword"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll LoI, race=troll
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Troll.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Troll"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll LoI, race=troll
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Troll.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Ice trolls are been recently discovered. It is thought that they evolved from"
" common trolls trapped in a region of freezing cold. A fully-grown ice troll "
"towers above a man, and, even unarmed, would be a great threat in combat. The"
" large clubs typically favored in fighting act as extensions of their arms, "
"used for the same purpose of mauling their prey into submission."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Troll.cfg:34
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Young_Man.cfg:243
msgid "club"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Shaman LoI, race=troll
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Troll_Shaman.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Troll Shaman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Shaman LoI, race=troll
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Troll_Shaman.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Ice trolls are been recently discovered. It is thought that they evolved from"
" common trolls trapped in a region of freezing cold. Ice troll shamans are "
"the mystical leaders of the ice trolls. Though not as strong or tough as "
"other ice trolls, their true power lies in their cold magic, which they use "
"to blast enemies with gouts of ice or to hide in the frozen forests."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Troll_Shaman.cfg:40
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Young_Man.cfg:24
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/deshra_juggernaut.cfg:30
msgid "fist"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Troll_Shaman.cfg:50
msgid "ice blast"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Warrior LoI, race=troll
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Warrior.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Troll Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Warrior LoI, race=troll
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Warrior.cfg:28
msgid ""
"Ice trolls are been recently discovered. It is thought that they evolved from"
" common trolls trapped in a region of freezing cold. Ice trolls typically "
"neither need nor prefer to use any proper armament in combat, as large "
"‘sticks and stones’ serve them all too well. However, ice trolls have been "
"seen on numerous occasions clad in rough-shod armor and bearing metal "
"hammers. It is speculated that orcish allies are the source and crafters of "
"these; expeditions into several forcibly-vacated ice troll caves have shown "
"little evidence of tool use, and certainly no metalworking of any kind. Given"
" how dangerous an ice troll is with its bare hands, the thought of one with "
"proper armament is entirely unsettling."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Wyvern LoI, race=elemental
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Wyvern.cfg:8
msgid "Ice Wyvern"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Wyvern LoI, race=elemental
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Wyvern.cfg:49
msgid ""
"Wyverns are large reptiles that resemble dragons, but are not the "
"intelligent, magical creatures. However, the fact that they are just wild "
"beasts should not cause any traveler who encounters one to dismiss the "
"threat, for they are fast and fierce when threatened or hungry.\n"
"\n"
"Although wyverns are social creatures, usually traveling in pairs or small "
"groups, their icy counterpart seems to be of solitary nature. Their hunting "
"patterns and diet are difficult to discern, for they often work with smaller "
"animals that would appear to be potential prey. That odd behavior may be an "
"adaptation to the harsh icy environments they inhabit."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Ice_Wyvern.cfg:92
msgid "slam"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Initiate, race=human
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mage_Initiate.cfg:5
msgid "Initiate"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Initiate, race=human
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mage_Initiate.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Initiates belong to the few individuals who are capable of using magic and "
"who had the luck of being discovered by a mage order. The amount of studying "
"that is still ahead of them may seem intimidating, but at the same time, the "
"mere existence of this knowledge is a testament to what humanity can achieve.\n"
"\n"
"Initiates are helpless in melee combat, but possess great offensive potential"
" that will grow as they get more experienced."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mage_Initiate.cfg:28
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Warlock.cfg:32
msgid "staff"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mage_Initiate.cfg:38
msgid "missile"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mage_Initiate.cfg:77
msgid "female^Initiate"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Saurian Matriarch LoI, race=lizard, gender=female
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Matriarch.cfg:4
msgid "female^Saurian Matriarch"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Matriarch.cfg:27
msgid "war talon"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Matriarch.cfg:36
msgid "curse"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Mehsi LoI, race=monster
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mehsi.cfg:4
msgid "Mehsi"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Mehsi LoI, race=monster
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mehsi.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Mehsi incite fear and awe in miners and explorers, figuring often in folklore"
" as wrathful deities of the underground. Capable of destroying carts "
"effortlessly, and possessed of seemingly endless strength and vitality, these"
" elusive leviathans are destructive and relentless to any who try to combat "
"them. Generally living in the deep, Mehsi are imposing even to the elite "
"dwarven warriors, and are the reason they seldom inhabit tunnels close to the"
" surface."
msgstr ""

#. [hides], id=dig
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mehsi.cfg:28
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mine_Worm.cfg:41
msgid "dig"
msgstr ""

#. [hides], id=dig
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mehsi.cfg:29
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mine_Worm.cfg:42
msgid "female^dig"
msgstr ""

#. [hides], id=dig
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mehsi.cfg:30
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mine_Worm.cfg:43
msgid ""
"This unit can hide underground, and remain undetected by its enemies.\n"
"\n"
"Enemy units cannot see this unit while it is underground, except if they have"
" units next to it. Any enemy unit that first discovers this unit immediately "
"loses all its remaining movement."
msgstr ""

#. [hides], id=dig
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mehsi.cfg:33
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mine_Worm.cfg:46
msgid ""
"On soft ground, this unit’s ambush skill renders it invisible to enemies "
"unless it is immediately adjacent or has revealed itself by attacking."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mehsi.cfg:44
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mine_Worm.cfg:57
msgid "stings"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Mine Worm LoI, race=monster
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mine_Worm.cfg:4
msgid "Mine Worm"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Mine Worm LoI, race=monster
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Mine_Worm.cfg:35
msgid ""
"Scholars differ as to the ancestry of the Mine Worm. Some hold that they were"
" brought to the mine by the demons. Others hold that they have always been "
"here. What is certain is that it is wise to avoid mines where they are known "
"to congregate."
msgstr ""

