#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Tesla_Coil.cfg:5
msgid "Tesla Coil"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Tesla Coil LoI, race=monster
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Tesla_Coil.cfg:36
msgid ""
"High amounts of an unknown kind of energy are created in this machine, and "
"used in an unknown way somewhere else. You have pretty much no idea what this"
" thing is meant to do. The light it creates seems to harm everyone nearby."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Thunderguard LoI, race=steelhive
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Thunderguard.cfg:4
msgid "Gobot Thunderguard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Thunderguard LoI, race=steelhive
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Thunderguard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This curious machine looks like a Dwarven Thunderguards made out of metal. "
"The Dwarven Thunderguards are famed for their curious weaponry, these strange"
" staves of wood and iron that make a thunderous noise in their anger. The "
"machinations behind this weaponry are a mystery, a secret taken to the grave "
"by the dwarves of Knalga who wield them, and are assumed to have even forged "
"them. The most that is known are reports of dwarves pouring a strange black "
"dust into the mouth of their weapons, which some say is a food to fuel the "
"beast imprisoned within. It seems that goblins tried to replicate them, "
"leading to a strange machine able to shoot lightnings.\n"
"\n"
"Though a single shot from these ‘thundersticks’ can take several minutes to "
"prepare, the results are seen by the goblins as being well worth the wait."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Orcish Commander LoI, race=orc
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Warlock.cfg:5
msgid "Orcish Commander"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Orcish Commander LoI, race=orc
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Warlock.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Some orcish shamans prefer to abandon their order, or are just expelled from "
"it for various reasons. Such orcs live as hermits in uninhabited places such "
"as swamps or caves. during their exile, they sometimes study the local flora,"
" learning about the properties of some herbs. Occasionally, some of them get "
"bored with their hermit lifestyle, and decided to sell their services to "
"wealthy orcish warlord. Their knowliege of herbalism is heavily valued amongs"
" their employers. They usually aren't used to heal the frontline, since "
"orcish commanders prefer to use most their troops as cannon fodder. They are "
"mostly used if the warlord who employed them is injured, or if the need to "
"keep alive a certain troop is strategically critical."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/units/Warlock.cfg:41
msgid "nature flare"
msgstr ""

