#. [object]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/utils/item_list.cfg:3377
msgid "Life of Uteaqniq Zei"
msgstr ""

#. [object]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/utils/item_list.cfg:3382
msgid ""
"Uteaqniq Zei knew everything about business. After a miserable childhood in "
"the streets of the imperial capital of Wesnoth, he spent most of his teenage "
"years transforming stolen eggs or smashed glass into warm meals.\n"
"\n"
"        During a brief mission in the 2nd legion, he learnt to trade and "
"mastered the art of finding terrific deals. But the gloom of military life "
"was incompatible with his desire of adventure. He therefore resigned to join "
"a small trading company in the west.\n"
"\n"
"        Sometime after arriving at Idaamub, Zei met the Dunefolks. He quickly"
" became aware that they had more to offer than exotic weapons and jewels that"
" other companies could not buy. By chance, he had seen the Dunefolks "
"manipulating materials looking like eggshells, thick as a human hand and "
"shining splendidly. Judging by the way they were bending them, Zei estimated "
"they were harder than granite. If he could get enough of them to pave the "
"floor of the house of some fortunate patrician, he would earn quite a sum. \n"
"\n"
"        Fortunately for Zei, the shells were worthless to the Dunefolks, who "
"were happy to get rid of them. Their joy doubled when Zei offered them in "
"exchange the same objects many companies had offered them in exchange for "
"their weapons and jewels. \n"
"\n"
"        With time, the Dunefolks made Uteaqniq one of their privileged "
"associate, and even went as far as giving him some weapons, despite having "
"refused other interested partners. Uteaqniq’s wealth never stopped growing "
"during those time, and at the time of the punishment of Dunefolks, he had "
"become one of the most fortunate citizens of Idaamub."
msgstr ""

#. [object]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/utils/item_list.cfg:3393
msgid "Opressor bow"
msgstr ""

#. [object]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/utils/item_list.cfg:3401
msgid "Just by looking at it, you know it hurts."
msgstr ""

#. [object]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/utils/item_list.cfg:3404
msgid "Story of the ofites"
msgstr ""

#. [object]
#: ./Legends_of_Idaamub/utils/item_list.cfg:3409
msgid ""
"Bearer of the written testimony of tens of generations of faithful, the "
"disciples of Of appear for the first time in the peaks of Gofeng more than "
"two centuries before the foundation of the Empires of Stars.\n"
"\n"
"        Very early in history, temples sacred to the eternal passion began "
"blooming on the side of the roads used by legionaries, giving room and "
"lodging to exhausted travelers who accepted to listen to the sermons "
"recounting Of’s marvels. One hundred years later, more than sixty villages of"
" the empire had thriving communities of fervent Of’s worshippers.\n"
"\n"
"        Of’s doctrine, based on the material reward of hard work, was far "
"simpler to believe than the one, more abstract and often less rewarding, of "
"the distant star emperors. The disciples only had to pretend they believed in"
" the strength of the defender and pass under its sacred shield and they were "
"accepted as members of His clan. \n"
"\n"
"        It is estimated that, at some occasions, children of fervent "
"worshippers were branded during secret ceremonies. These children only "
"received this mortal injury to better resurrect passing under the sacred "
"shield."
msgstr ""

